1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,200
Warm fluid rises, cool fluid sinks—what's really happening?

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:06,800
This is convection, one of nature's most powerful forces.

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,000
Think boiling water.

4
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,200
The heat causes water at the bottom to rise, while cooler water descends.

5
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,000
Weather patterns?

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:14,800
Same principle!

7
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Warm air rises, creating clouds, while cool air sinks.

8
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:22,400
Convection isn't just science; it's life around us in action.

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:26,000
Want to dive deeper into the mysteries of physics?

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,200
